  "texts": [
    "(2) each of the panelists will have six minutes to share their approach, (3) followed by our two invited discussants, and (4) a Q&A with the audience and presenters.",
    "Making AI-Based Apps Strengthens Children's Data Agency and Understanding of AI Matti Tedre, Henriikka Vartiainen This socioculturally informed study introduces a pedagogical framework, design principles, and a crossboundary co-design process involving teachers and researchers to co-develop new educational practices, curriculum materials, and technology for teaching AI in Finnish basic education.",
    "In a multidisciplinary, designbased research project, 213 students in 4th and 7th grades explored the basics of AI by co-designing and creating their own AI-driven applications while considering AI's impact and ethics.",
    "Grounded in design-oriented pedagogy, the aim was to position children as designers and knowledge creators in AI (Kahila et al., 2024).",
    "The intervention started by introducing learners to uses of classifiers in contexts familiar to them."
  ]
}